记者：吴斌  本文来源：财联社“ 世界卫生组织（WHO）周五警告，遏制新型冠状病毒的“机会之窗”正在关闭，需要迅速采取行动。
Coronavirus' window of opportunity 'to contain the new coronavirus is closing, the World Health Organisation warned Friday, calling for swift action.
”世界卫生组织（WHO）周五警告，遏制新型冠状病毒的“机会之窗”正在关闭，需要迅速采取行动。
The World Health Organisation warned on Friday that the "window of opportunity" to contain the new coronavirus is closing and requires swift action.
当被问及现在是否处在爆发“临界点”时，世界卫生组织总干事谭德塞表示，他仍然相信该病毒可能会被控制，但“机会之窗正在缩小，因此我们需要迅速采取行动，阻止机会之窗完全关闭。
Asked if there was a "tipping point" now, World Health Organization Director-General Thant said he still believed the virus might be under control, but "the window of opportunity is narrowing, so we need to act quickly to stop it from closing completely."
”谭德塞说：“这次爆发可能朝任何方向发展。
"This outbreak could go in any direction," said Tanner.
如果做得好，我们可以避免任何严重的危机，但是如果我们错失良机，那么我们将面临严重的问题。
If we do well, we can avoid any serious crisis, but if we miss a good opportunity, we will face serious problems.
”全球面临挑战尽管近来中国防疫形势整体好转，但日韩等其他地区却面临巨大挑战。
Global Challenges While China's epidemic prevention situation has improved overall recently, other regions, such as Japan and South Korea, face daunting challenges.
截至当地时间21日22时，日本新型冠状病毒感染确诊人数上升至739人，包括邮轮“钻石公主”号上634例病例。
The number of confirmed coronavirus infections in Japan rose to 739 at 2200 local time, including 634 cases on board the cruise ship Princess Diamond.
受疫情影响，日本执政党自民党当天决定，原定于3月8日在东京召开的有该党国会议员及地方议员等3000多人出席的党大会延期。
Affected by the outbreak, Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) decided that March 8 in Tokyo, the party's Congress, which was scheduled to be attended by more than 3,000 members of parliament and local councillors, postponed.
韩国中央防疫对策本部21日通报，截至21日下午4点，韩国新增48例新冠肺炎确诊病例，累计确诊增至204例。
As of 4: 00 pm on the 21st, the number of confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia in South Korea has risen to 204, the Ministry of Central Prevention and Control of Disease reported.
谭德塞表示，伊朗在过去两天报告了18例病例和4例死亡，这“令人十分担忧”，并补充说世界卫生组织已向伊朗提供了检测试剂盒。
Mr Tanner said Iran had reported 18 cases and four deaths in the past two days, which was "very worrying" and added that the World Health Organization had provided test kits to Iran.
黎巴嫩卫生部长哈马德·哈桑说，黎巴嫩周五证实了其首例冠状病毒病例，并表示正在监测另外两个疑似病例，此前一名四十五岁的妇女于周四从伊朗圣城库姆返回黎巴嫩，检测结果呈阳性。
Lebanon's health minister, Hamad Hassan, said Lebanon confirmed its first case of coronavirus Friday and said it was monitoring two other suspected cases after a 45-year-old woman returned to Lebanon Thursday from the holy city of Qom and tested positive.
谭德塞还表示，由世卫组织牵头的国际专家小组及其中国同行将在周六访问武汉。
Tan also said a WHO-led international panel of experts and their Chinese counterparts will visit Wuhan on Saturday.
该团队于上周末抵达中国，其成员包括来自美国疾病控制中心（CDC）以及德国、日本、尼日利亚、俄罗斯、新加坡和韩国的专家。
The team arrived in China at the weekend and included experts from the U.S. Centers for Disease Control (CDC) and Germany, Japan, Nigeria, Russia, Singapore and South Korea.
